hands_on_practices.solution:
1. At low $T$ the two magnon branches ($S^z=\pm1$) are dilute and bosonic, so
$$n_\pm(k)\approx e^{-\beta\bigl(E_0(k)\mp h\bigr)},\qquad \beta=\frac1{k_B T}.$$
The magnetization per site is
$$M_z=\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{dk}{2\pi}\bigl[n_+(k)-n_-(k)\bigr]
=\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{dk}{2\pi}\Bigl[e^{-\beta(E_0(k)-h)}-e^{-\beta(E_0(k)+h)}\Bigr].$$

2. Expand to first order in $h$:
$$M_z\approx2\beta h\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{dk}{2\pi}\,e^{-\beta E_0(k)}.$$

3. Near the minimum $k=k_0$, set $q=k-k_0$ and $E_0(k)\approx\Delta_E+Aq^2$, extend $q\in(-\infty,\infty)$:
$$\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{dk}{2\pi}e^{-\beta E_0(k)}
\approx e^{-\beta\Delta_E}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\frac{dq}{2\pi}e^{-\beta A q^2}
=e^{-\beta\Delta_E}\frac1{2\pi}\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{\beta A}}
=\frac{e^{-\beta\Delta_E}}{2\sqrt{\pi\,\beta A}}.$$

4. Hence
$$M_z\approx2\beta h\,\frac{e^{-\beta\Delta_E}}{2\sqrt{\pi\,\beta A}}
=\frac{h}{\sqrt{\pi A}}\,\beta^{1/2}e^{-\beta\Delta_E}.$$

5. The parallel susceptibility is
$$\chi_z=\frac{\partial M_z}{\partial h}\Big|_{h=0}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi A}}\,\beta^{1/2}e^{-\beta\Delta_E}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi A k_B T}}\exp\!\Bigl(-\frac{\Delta_E}{k_B T}\Bigr).$$
